you tonight. It's really important.

251
00:19:57,378 --> 00:19:59,869
OK, Sam. It's Sam.

252
00:20:00,047 --> 00:20:04,313
Across town, Miranda met
her karmic treasure for dinner.

253
00:20:04,485 --> 00:20:07,045
After ten years,
I made partner two months ago.

254
00:20:07,221 --> 00:20:09,951
Or was it three? I'm losing track.

255
00:20:10,124 --> 00:20:11,887
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

256
00:20:12,059 --> 00:20:16,359
- Can I get you another drink?
- Double vodka martini, please.

257
00:20:16,531 --> 00:20:20,433
- And you, sir?
- I'm fine.

258
00:20:21,903 --> 00:20:24,736
- Would you care to order?
- Could we have a minute?

259
00:20:25,806 --> 00:20:28,104
Take your time.

260
00:20:28,276 --> 00:20:32,940
I thought about law school.
I loved Columbo so much as a kid...

261
00:20:33,114 --> 00:20:37,676
Miranda realized that every woman
was staring at her date.

262
00:20:37,885 --> 00:20:41,184
Your friend is the typical case
that I see on the job.

263
00:20:41,355 --> 00:20:44,950
It's not as exciting as you might think.
It's not homicide...

264
00:20:45,126 --> 00:20:51,622
She knewwhat they were thinking -
why is that attractive man with her?

265
00:20:51,799 --> 00:20:54,859
If your friend hadn't lost her shoes,
I wouldn't be here.

266
00:20:55,036 --> 00:20:58,199
There you go.

267
00:20:58,406 --> 00:21:00,203
Thank you.

268
00:21:01,409 --> 00:21:04,901
She drank to feel better about herself.

269
00:21:11,986 --> 00:21:17,151
Six vodka martinis later,
she was feeling pretty damn good.

270
00:21:17,325 --> 00:21:20,317
- You're hot.
- And you're a little drunk.

271
00:21:20,494 --> 00:21:23,327
I'm fine. I'm great.

272
00:21:24,799 --> 00:21:27,063
Hot, hot, hot.

273
00:21:27,234 --> 00:21:30,726
You may be the most beautiful man
that I've ever been with.

274
00:21:30,905 --> 00:21:32,930
You're not bad yourself.

275
00:21:33,107 --> 00:21:37,737
I'm no Mena Suvari,
but I'm great in bed.

276
00:21:43,217 --> 00:21:48,018
When Trey didn't come to bed,
Charlotte went looking for him.

277
00:21:57,064 --> 00:22:01,296
- What are you doing out here?
- Improving my serve.

278
00:22:02,603 --> 00:22:07,063
Stop. You're upset,
and what I did was so wrong.

279
00:22:07,241 --> 00:22:09,641
- I'm sorry.
- What can I say?

280
00:22:09,810 --> 00:22:12,711
I'm unable to meet your needs,
so from time to time,

281
00:22:12,880 --> 00:22:18,011
as much as I detest it,
I'll have to look the other way.

282
00:22:18,185 --> 00:22:20,653
I don't want a husband
who looks the other way.

283
00:22:20,821 --> 00:22:24,518
I want a husband who makes me
not want to kiss the gardener.

284
00:22:36,470 --> 00:22:38,631
No marriage is perfect.

285
00:22:40,141 --> 00:22:43,133
So much of what we have
is wonderful.

286
00:22:43,310 --> 00:22:47,713
We can have separate lives
and still be together.

287
00:22:47,882 --> 00:22:50,612
It's totally acceptable.

288
00:22:50,785 --> 00:22:53,754
As Charlotte looked at
her perfect husband

289
00:22:53,888 --> 00:22:57,085
at their family's
perfect country house,

290
00:22:57,258 --> 00:22:59,522
she realized
the one thing that was missing

291
00:22:59,694 --> 00:23:03,596
was that perfect connection
with an imperfect person.

292
00:23:06,801 --> 00:23:11,135
When we get back to the city,
I think we should separate for a while.

293
00:23:14,775 --> 00:23:16,106
All righty.

294
00:23:21,916 --> 00:23:27,115
Seven unreturned phone calls,
and still no response from Natasha.

295
00:23:27,288 --> 00:23:31,156
Buddhists believe you pay for what
you do wrong in this life in the next.

296
00:23:31,325 --> 00:23:35,455
I knewwhat I'd done. I just didn't think
I could wait a lifetime to be forgiven.

297
00:23:42,937 --> 00:23:48,500
The next morning, Miranda woke up
with the worst hangover of her life.

298
00:23:53,280 --> 00:23:55,441
Detective Stevens?

299
00:24:01,422 --> 00:24:06,621
On her hall table, she discovered that
Detective Stevens had left a number...

300
00:24:07,428 --> 00:24:10,192
...for her local AA chapter.

301
00:24:11,499 --> 00:24:14,059
Samantha got her karmic retribution.

302
00:24:14,235 --> 00:24:17,136
I love you, Sam Jones.

303
00:24:17,304 --> 00:24:21,001
In screwing Sam Jones,
she wound up screwing herself.

304
00:24:21,175 --> 00:24:23,439
I love you, Sam Jones.

305
00:24:27,381 --> 00:24:31,715
A few days later, Charlotte came
home to her old apartment.

306
00:24:31,886 --> 00:24:37,290
It was good fortune that she had only
sublet it, not to mention good sense.

307
00:24:40,261 --> 00:24:43,697
Not wanting to come back
in my next life as a dung beetle,

308
00:24:43,864 --> 00:24:46,890
I asked Samantha's assistant
to pump Natasha's assistant

309
00:24:47,067 --> 00:24:50,036
to find out
where she was having lunch.

310
00:25:01,148 --> 00:25:03,309
I need to talk to you.

311
00:25:03,551 --> 00:25:06,577
- I'm gonna scream.
- I'm only gonna stay a minute.

312
00:25:06,754 --> 00:25:08,881
I tried to call you at work, but...

313
00:25:10,191 --> 00:25:12,421
Anyway, it's not important.

314
00:25:14,094 --> 00:25:17,120
Can I have a sip of this?

315
00:25:26,574 --> 00:25:28,269
Thanks.

316
00:25:33,781 --> 00:25:36,511
I heard about your marriage.

317
00:25:37,885 --> 00:25:42,322
It's just so terrible.

318
00:25:43,457 --> 00:25:45,982
I never meant
for any of this to happen.

319
00:25:46,126 --> 00:25:50,495
If there was something
I could do to take it away, I would.

320
00:25:50,664 --> 00:25:51,961
But I can't.

321
00:25:53,367 --> 00:25:58,270
I came here today because
I needed to say how sorry I am.

322
00:25:59,373 --> 00:26:02,968
I am deeply sorry
for what I did to you.

323
00:26:03,477 --> 00:26:05,604
It was wrong.

324
00:26:06,447 --> 00:26:08,472
I'm sorry.

325
00:26:12,419 --> 00:26:15,217
Are you through?

326
00:26:15,389 --> 00:26:19,291
Yes. Thank you for listening.

327
00:26:23,063 --> 00:26:25,054
Wait.

328
00:26:26,300 --> 00:26:28,063
I'm sorry, too.

329
00:26:29,904 --> 00:26:31,337
You are?

330
00:26:31,505 --> 00:26:35,498
Yes. I'm sorry about it all.

331
00:26:37,778 --> 00:26:41,908
I'm sorry he moved to Paris
and fell in love with me.

332
00:26:42,116 --> 00:26:44,812
I'm sorry that we ever got married.

333
00:26:47,121 --> 00:26:49,282
I'm sorry he cheated on me with you,

334
00:26:49,456 --> 00:26:53,620
and I'm sorry that I pretended
to ignore it for as long as I did.

335
00:26:55,462 --> 00:26:57,987
I'm sorry I found you in my apartment,

336
00:26:58,165 --> 00:27:00,895
fell down the stairs
and broke my tooth.

337
00:27:02,770 --> 00:27:06,001
I'm very sorry
that after much painful dental surgery

338
00:27:06,173 --> 00:27:09,631
this tooth is still
a different color than this tooth.

339
00:27:10,678 --> 00:27:16,116
Finally, I'm sorry that you felt
the need to come down here.

340
00:27:16,350 --> 00:27:20,616
Not only have you
ruined my marriage,

341
00:27:20,788 --> 00:27:23,586
you've ruined my lunch.

342
00:27:27,094 --> 00:27:30,393
That's just what I had to say.

343
00:27:32,433 --> 00:27:34,697
I was just leaving.

344
00:27:37,471 --> 00:27:43,603
My actions had set into motion
a karmic chain of events

345
00:27:43,777 --> 00:27:46,678
that put Natasha
back on the singles market.

346
00:27:46,847 --> 00:27:49,645
As if single women
didn't have it hard enough.

347
00:28:00,995 --> 00:28:04,795
Somewhere out there,
Big was alone again.

348
00:28:04,965 --> 00:28:07,433
The universe may not
always play fair,

349
00:28:07,601 --> 00:28:11,093
but at least it's got
a hell of a sense of humor.



